Two directors of Directline Assurance were on Tuesday aqcuitted in a case where they were accused of obstructing officers of the Insurance Regulatory Authority (IRA). Senior Principal Magistrate Martha Nanzushi released Anthony Macharia and Bashir Mburu saying the prosecution had failed to prove their case. The charges relate to a 2019 case in which Macharia and Mburu were accused of blocking IRA officers from conducting an inspection at Directline Assurance Company limited. Royal Media Services Chairman Dr. SK Macharia and Directline Assurance Limited are seeking private prosecution of over 10 suspects whom the Director of Public Prosecution Noordin Haji had declined to prosecute despite what they termed overwhelming evidence against the suspects. As the case began, the intended accused applied to be heard and the applicants were directed to serve the accused with the application. The charges against the intended accused relate to the handling of shares and finances at the Direct Assurance Company Limited and criminal offences that date as far back as the year 2011. Also Read: The accused allegedly engaged in fraudulent transfer of shareholding and monies amounting to over Ksh.4 Billion between the year 2012 and 2018. Video Of The Day: Former sports CS Hassan Wario convicted over Rio games scam